    <h1>About</h1>
    <div class="article-wrap">
      <p>My research interests include Security and Privacy, Trustworthy AI, Software Engineering and Formal Methods. 
I obtained my PhD degree from National University of Singapore, Singapore, and my M.S. and B.S. degrees from Peking University, China. 
I am an Associate Editor of <a href="https://www.computer.org/csdl/journal/tq" target="_blank"> IEEE Transactions on Dependable and Secure Computing</a>, <a href="https://www.computer.org/csdl/journal/sc" target="_blank">IEEE Transactions on Service Computing</a>, and <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/journal/neural-networks" target="_blank"> Neural Networks</a>.</p>

<p><br />
<b>I am recently working on these areas: </b></p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Privacy Compliance of Emerging App Ecosystems</b></li>  
  <ul>
    <li> LLM-based Apps: ASE24 (ACM SIGSOFT Distinguished Paper) </li>
    <li> Virtual Personal Assistant Apps: <a href="/files/ICSE24-PICO.pdf" target="_blank">PICO</a>@ICSE24, QuPer@PETS24, <a href="/files/ASE22-Skipper.pdf" target="_blank">Skipper</a>@ASE22, <a href="/files/ASE22-VITAS.pdf" target="_blank">VITAS</a>@ASE22 </li>
    <li> Web-based Apps: <a href="/files/SIGMETRICS23.pdf" target="_blank">SIGMETRICS23</a>, <a href="/files/ASE22-PPCompliance.pdf" target="_blank">ExtPPCompliance</a>@ASE22, <a href="/files/WWW21.pdf" target="_blank">WPF</a>@WWW21 </li>
    <li> Android: <a href="/files/DopCheck-FSE24.pdf" target="_blank">DopCheck</a>@FSE24, <a href="/files/NDSS23-U2I2.pdf" target="_blank">U2-I2</a>@NDSS23 </li>
  </ul>
  
<li><b>Trustworthy and Responsible AI</b></li> 
    <ul>
      <li> AI Model Usage Control: <a href="/files/CoreLocker-SP24.pdf" target="_blank">CoreLocker</a>@IEEE S&amp;P24 [<a href="https://www.zihan.com.au/SP24CoreLocker.html">CoreLocker Website</a>]  </li> 
      <li> Robustness Verification: <a href="/files/WraLU-POPL24.pdf" target="_blank">WraLU</a>@POPL24 </li>
      <li> Privacy Compliance: <a href="https://www.usenix.org/conference/usenixsecurity24/presentation/liu-shuofeng" target="_blank">AlgoSpec</a>@Usenix Security24, <a href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3564625.3564658" target="_blank">AgrAmplifier</a>@ACSAC22, <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9822964" target="_blank">TDSC22</a></li> 
      <li> Reliable AI Model Deployment: <a href="/files/ICSE23-MOB.pdf" target="_blank">ML Model Optimization Bugs</a>@ICSE23 </li>
    </ul>

    <li><b>IoT/ICS Security</b></li>  
    <ul>
      <li> <a href="/files/PFCon-WWW24.pdf" target="_blank">PFCon</a>@WWW24 </li>
      <li> <a href="/files/ISSTA21-Taifu.pdf" target="_blank">Taifu</a> (Taifu stands for 太傅‚ the Grand Tutor of the emperor in imperial China, who is in charge of providing a young emperor with moral guidance)@ISSTA21, [<a href="https://sites.google.com/view/taifu-demo">Taifu Website</a>] </li>
      <li> <a href="https://www.comp.nus.edu.sg/~tsunami/papers/TSE-Final.pdf" target="_blank">HomeScan</a>@TSE19 </li>
      <li> <a href="http://www.illinois.adsc.com.sg/papers/acsac17_attestation.pdf" target="_blank">ACSAC17</a> </li> 
    </ul>
  
  <li><b>Mobile Security</b></li>  
  <ul>
    <li> <a href="/files/NDSS23-U2I2.pdf" target="_blank">U2-I2</a>@NDSS23, [<a href="https://uq-trust-lab.github.io/u2i2">U2-I2 Website</a>]  </li>
    <li> <a href="/files/MobiCom22.pdf" target="_blank">MobiCom22</a> </li>
    <li> <a href="https://dl.acm.org/doi/pdf/10.1109/ASE.2019.00017" target="_blank">ASE19</a> </li>
    <li> <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/7911333" target="_blank">DroidPF</a>@TSE18 </li>
  </ul>
  
 </ul>

